Bundled fonts — licensing & attribution
========================================

These web fonts are open-source metric-compatible substitutes for the
proprietary Microsoft Office fonts. They are vendored (converted to woff2) from
the set LibreOffice ships, so the editor renders deterministically without
fetching fonts from a third-party CDN.

- Carlito (≈ Calibri)        — SIL Open Font License 1.1.  © tyPoland, Łukasz Dziedzic.
- Caladea (≈ Cambria)        — SIL Open Font License 1.1.  © Carolina Giovagnoli / Huerta Tipográfica.
- Liberation Sans  (≈ Arial)         — SIL Open Font License 1.1. © Red Hat, Inc.
- Liberation Serif (≈ Times New Roman)— SIL Open Font License 1.1. © Red Hat, Inc.
- Liberation Mono  (≈ Courier New)   — SIL Open Font License 1.1. © Red Hat, Inc.

Full OFL 1.1 text: https://openfontlicense.org/open-font-license-official-text/
The OFL permits bundling and redistribution (including in commercial products);
the fonts may not be sold by themselves and the reserved names must be retained.
